dct_title_s: Zone de Neufchâteau, Carte de France 1:50,000.
dct_description_sm: Scale: 1:50000;  Projection: Lambert conformal conic projection;  Map Type: lcgft;  Other Descriptive Notes about Map Series: Relief shown by hachures and spot heights.  Covers area north from Goussaincourt to Vrécourt to the south, and west from Charmois to Biécourt to the east. Neufchâteau roughly above center of sheet.  Likely reprint with additional overprinting of sheet XXXII-17, Neufchâteau from series Carte de France au 1/50.000, originally published Institut Géographique National, 1952.  Has red overprint grid, and red magnetic declination diagram in center right margin. Lacks legend.  La déclination magnétique correspond au centre de la feuille et au 1er janvier 1917..  Quadrillage kilometrique Système Lambert..
dct_isPartOf_sm: Field Maps of Colonel Roland T. Fenton
